# Template for the dogfood instance's single declared environment file.
# Install as $FQ_DOGFOOD/.secrets/env (chmod 600). Both launchers source
# it with `set -a`, so it is a POSIX shell fragment: command substitution
# works, and every assignment is exported.
#
# This file is the ONLY place the daemon and watcher get their
# environment from (#102) — if a variable isn't declared here, the
# process doesn't have it.

# LLM provider keys — one per provider declared in fq.toml. A provider
# key missing here fails the daemon at startup (the pricing guarantee),
# not silently at invocation time.
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-REPLACE-ME

# GitHub auth for the watcher and for agents' `gh pr create`.
# Deriving it from the current gh login survives token rotation at the
# cost of one ambient lookup; replace with a literal token (or a token
# file refreshed out-of-band) for full hermeticity — open question 1 on
# issue #102.
GH_TOKEN="$(gh auth token)"

# Watcher tuning (defaults shown; uncomment to override).
# FQ_WATCH_REPO=bricef/factor-q
# FQ_WATCH_AGENT=m0-issue-fix
# FQ_NATS_URL=nats://127.0.0.1:4223
# FQ_WATCH_POLL=60s
